==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Minibus
<hw>Min"i*bus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>minor</ets>
less + <ets>-bus</ets>, as in <ets>omnibus</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A kind of light passenger vehicle, carrying four persons.</def>
<mark>[archaic]</mark> ⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A type of bus (omnibus) similar in general
appearnace to a standard-sized bus, but smaller and having a smaller
passenger capacity, typically about 15 persons. It is usually used for
transportation over relatively short distances.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>minicomputer</ent>⟦br⟧
